Manchester United have confirmed that 21-year-old goalkeeper, Nathan Bishop, has signed a new deal with the club. Bishop will now remain at Old Trafford until June 2023. Man United disclosed this in a statement on Monday ahead of their Premier League clash with Burnley on Tuesday. The statement read: “Nathan Bishop has penned a new Manchester United contract and the young goalkeeper has set his sights on a number of targets for the coming few years. “The 21-year-old stopper has signed a new deal until June 2023 with an option for a further year.” Bishop joined Man United from Southend United a year ago.